  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0d82\u0da2\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dda\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dba\u0ddd \u0d85\u0d9c\u0ddd\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd4\u0db4 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Engineering Corporation employees demand August salary",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The employees of the State Engineering Corporation staged a protest today (29) in front of the corporation's head office in Colombo 2, demanding the payment of August salary.",
        "The employees of the engineering corporation protested by displaying placards with slogans such as 'Inflation is sky high, no salary on the right day, the thief ate the nut, the salary is paid outside the ration, the construction was stopped, our jobs were lost and the workers are not paid, the managers have no answer'.",
        "An official of the State Engineering Corporation said that although the August salary should have been received on the 25th, the authorities have not yet announced the date of payment and the July salary was paid in two parts and the second part was given on the 25th.",
        "The official said that the engineering corporation will not work after the government has stopped the construction for two years and said that if such decisions were taken, the government should also take measures regarding its employees.",
        "The official further said that the board of directors will not give a solution to this problem without even giving a discussion to the employees."
      ],
